H0.text: Pupa is the stage of the insect life cycle in which insects begin developing their wings.

H1.text: Crystalline is the stage of insects' life cycle at which they begin developing their wings.

H2.text: Larva is the stage of the insect life cycle during which insects begin developing their wings.

H3.text: Pupal is the stage of the insect life cycle in which insects begin developing their wings.

A4.text: In hemimetabolous insects, external wing buds form in later instars of nymphs.

A5.text: It is during the pupal stage that the adult structures of the insect are formed while the larval structures are broken down.

A6.text: The adult structures grow from imaginal discs.
